        "Resonating Covenant Heroic Tier Prerequisite : Invoker, Divine Covenant class feature Benefit : Whenever you use a divine encounter or daily attack power on your turn, you gain a +1 feat bonus to your next attack roll with an at-will divine power before the end of your next turn. Player's Handbook 2, page(s) 188.",
    feat2058:
        "Resourceful Donation Heroic Tier Prerequisite : Warlord, Resourceful Presence class feature Benefit : Whenever you spend a healing surge, you can divide the hit points regained between yourself and one ally adjacent to you in any proportion. Dragon Magazine 381, page(s) 29.",
    feat2547:
        "Resourceful Leader [Multiclass Warlord] Heroic Tier Prerequisite : Int 13 or Cha 13 Benefit : You gain training in one skill from the warlord's class skills list. When an ally you can see spends an action point to make an attack, the ally gains a +3 bonus to damage rolls on a hit or gains 3 temporary hit points on a miss. This bonus increases to +5 at 11th level and +7 at 21st level. These temporary hit points increase to 5 at 11th level and 7 at 21st level. Martial Power 2, page(s) 146.",
    feat1023:
        "Restful Healing Heroic Tier Benefit : After you take a short rest or an extended rest, any healing power you use before the start of your next encounter restores the maximum number of hit points possible. For example, if a 6th-level cleric with Wisdom 18 and this feat uses healing word after a rest, that power allows the target to regain hit points equal to his or her healing surge value plus 16 (the maximum result of 2d6 + 4). Player's Handbook 2, page(s) 188.",
    feat2012:
        "Restless Dead Heroic Tier Prerequisite : Revenant, must worship the Raven Queen Benefit : While you are at 0 hit points or fewer and still conscious, you gain a +2 bonus to attack rolls and all defenses. Dragon Magazine 380, page(s) 64.",
    feat3710:
        "Restoration Mastery Prerequisite : Ritual Caster feat, mastery of Comrades' Succor and one other restoration ritual Benefit : When you succeed on a Heal check to grant second wind, the subject gains the defense bonus that second wind normally grants. If you succeed on a Heal check to grant a saving throw, the target gains a +2 power bonus to that saving throw. You can also master and perform restoration rituals as if your level were two higher. Dragon Magazine 405.",
    feat3112:
        "Resurgent Memory Heroic Tier Prerequisite : Deva, memory of a thousand lifetimes power, any psionic class Benefit : When you use memory of a thousand lifetimes, you can shift 1 square as a free action. If the triggering attack roll misses or saving throw or check fails, you gain temporary hit points equal to the higher of your Intelligence or Wisdom modifier. Dragon Magazine 388.",
