        "Vigilante Justice Style Prerequisite : Any martial class Benefit : You gain a benefit with any of the following powers you possess. Brash Strike (fighter): If an adjacent enemy marked by you makes an attack that doesn't include you as a target, you can use this exploit in place of the melee basic attack that Combat Challenge allows. Circling Strike (ranger): If an enemy hits you or your beast companion during that enemy's turn, you deal extra damage equal to your Wisdom modifier if you hit with this exploit during your next turn. Commander's Strike (warlord): If, on its last turn, the target hit the ally you choose to benefit from this exploit, that ally has combat advantage against that target for the melee basic attack this exploit allows. Riposte Strike (rogue): If you hit with this exploit, you can riposte if the target attacks you or any ally adjacent to you before the start of your next turn. Dragon Magazine 373, page(s) 20.",
